SECTION 2 — EMBEDDED MODEL AND DATA ASSETS (NOT RUST CRATES)
==============================================================

Three non-code assets are embedded directly in the POC-COM binary. These
are not Cargo dependencies and don't appear in Cargo.lock, so they're
listed separately here.

1. WHISPER SPEECH-RECOGNITION MODEL
   Files: crates/lexicon_modem/assets/whisper/model.safetensors,
          config.json, tokenizer.json, melfilters.bytes
   Source: openai/whisper-base.en (OpenAI), converted to the safetensors
           format for use with the `candle` ML framework (see Section 1
           for candle-core/candle-nn/candle-transformers' own MIT OR
           Apache-2.0 licensing).
   License: MIT License. OpenAI released the Whisper model family
            (weights, code, and associated files) under the MIT License.
            The full MIT License text is reproduced in Section 3 below.

2. LAND OUTLINE DATA (for the Maidenhead grid contact map)
   File: crates/app_gui/assets/land_outlines.bin
   Source: Natural Earth (naturalearthdata.com), 1:110m Cultural/Physical
           Vectors, "ne_110m_land" dataset, converted to a compact binary
           format by this project's own crates/app_gui/src/bin/
           convert_land_geojson.rs tool.
   License: Public domain. Natural Earth's own terms of use state: "No
            permission is needed to use Natural Earth. Crediting the
            authors is unnecessary." No further action is required for
            this asset.

3. PRE-RENDERED SPEECH CLIPS (POC-COM's own spoken vocabulary)
   File: crates/lexicon_modem/assets/clips.bin
   Source: Generated once, offline, by this project's own
           crates/lexicon_modem/src/dev_tts.rs tool, which called the
           Windows SAPI/WinRT text-to-speech engine (a built-in Windows OS
           component, e.g. the "Microsoft Zira" system voice) to render
           this project's small fixed vocabulary (NATO phonetic letters,
           digit words, and marker words -- see
           crates/lexicon_modem/src/vocabulary.rs) to real audio, exactly
           once. This audio is then embedded and played back directly --
           no TTS engine runs at send time in the shipped application.

